  <name>gh-notif</name>
  <summary>A high-performance CLI tool for managing GitHub notifications</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      gh-notif helps you efficiently manage GitHub notifications with powerful
      filtering, sorting, and grouping capabilities. It provides a modern
      terminal UI and supports concurrent operations for improved performance.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>High-performance notification listing with efficient filtering</li>
      <li>Advanced filtering with boolean expressions and named filters</li>
      <li>Smart grouping and notification scoring</li>
      <li>Real-time watch mode with desktop notifications</li>
      <li>Interactive terminal UI with responsive layouts</li>
      <li>Comprehensive actions (mark as read, archive, subscribe/unsubscribe)</li>
      <li>Platform-specific secure credential storage</li>
      <li>Performance optimizations with caching and concurrent operations</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
